 While a polynomial 
\begin_inset Formula $p^{2}+q^{2}$
\end_inset

 is an unbounded operator on the Hilbert space 
\begin_inset Formula $L^{2}$
\end_inset

,
 it is a continuous operator on the Fréchet space of entire functions.
 The Arens–Michael completion includes power series in 
\begin_inset Formula $p$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $q$
\end_inset

 that converge to new continuous operators on that space.
\end_layout

