 How did this work?
 The transistors are made of atoms.
 By convention,
 the atoms evolve in a unitary fashion.
 The common trope is that unitarity does not allow the erasure of information,
 and Schrodinger's Cat is supposed to be the expression of that.
 But the problem here is that we never defined what information was.
 Harking back to the earlier model of a universe empty but for a handful of protons and electrons,
 it appears that 
